{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Observing user input"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VisualNavigator"},{"text":" implements ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"InputObservable"},{"text":", providing a way to intercept input events.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Implementing an input observer","anchor":"Implementing-an-input-observer","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here’s an example of a simple ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"InputObserving"},{"text":" implementation that logs all key and pointer events emitted by the navigator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["navigator.addObserver(InputObserver())","","@MainActor final class InputObserver: InputObserving {","    func didReceive(_ event: PointerEvent) async -> Bool {","        print(\"Received pointer event: \\(event)\")","        return false","    }","","    func didReceive(_ event: KeyEvent) async -> Bool {","        print(\"Received key event: \\(event)\")","        return false","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you choose to handle a specific event, return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" to prevent subsequent observers from using it. This is useful when you want to avoid triggering multiple actions upon receiving an event.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"code":"InputObserving","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implementation receives low-level events that can be used to create higher-level gesture recognizers, such as taps or pinches. To assist you, the toolkit also offers helpers to observe tap, click and key press events.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Observing tap and click events","anchor":"Observing-tap-and-click-events","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ActivatePointerObserver"},{"text":" is an implementation of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"InputObserving"},{"text":" recognizing single taps or clicks. You can use the convenient static factories to observe these events.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["navigator.addObserver(.tap { event in","    print(\"User tapped at \\(event.location)\")","    return false","})","","\/\/ Key modifiers can be used to recognize an event only when a modifier key is pressed.","navigator.addObserver(.click(modifiers: [.shift]) { event in","    print(\"User clicked at \\(event.location)\")","    return false","})"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Observing keyboard events","anchor":"Observing-keyboard-events","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Similarly, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"KeyObserver"},{"text":" implementation provides an easy method to intercept keyboard events.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["navigator.addObserver(.key { event in","    print(\"User pressed the key \\(event.key) with modifiers \\(event.modifiers)\")","    return false","})"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can also be used to observe a specific keyboard shortcut."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["navigator.addObserver(.key(.a) {","    self.log(.info, \"User pressed A\")","    return false","})","","navigator.addObserver(.key(.a, [.control, .shift]) {","    self.log(.info, \"User pressed Control+Shift+A\")","    return false","})"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Highlights","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Decorations","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts"],"anchor":"Essentials","generated":true,"title":"Essentials"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In visual publications like EPUB or PDF, users can interact with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VisualNavigator"},{"type":"text","text":" instance using gestures, a keyboard, a mouse, a pencil, or a trackpad. When the publication does not override user input events, you may want to intercept them to trigger actions in your user interface. For example, you can turn pages or toggle the navigation bar on taps, or open a bookmarks screen when pressing the Command-Shift-D hotkey."}],"references":{"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/NavigatorOverview":{"type":"topic","title":"Navigator Overview","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about the architecture, configuration, and usage of the Readium Navigator."}],"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigatoroverview","kind":"article"},"Decorations.md":{"url":"Decorations.md","identifier":"Decorations.md","title":"Decorations guide","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Decorations guide"}],"type":"link"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/uiviewrepresentable":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","title":"UIViewRepresentable","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"UIViewRepresentable","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"link"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/EPUB-Fonts":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Readium allows users to customize the font family used to render a reflowable EPUB, by changing the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"Preferences.md"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/epub-fonts","title":"Font families in the EPUB navigator","kind":"article"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Highlights":{"type":"topic","title":"Implementing Highlights","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/highlights","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Highlighting lets users mark up passages in a publication for later reference - a core feature of any reading app. In Readium, highlights are built on top of the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Decoration API"}]},{"type":"text","text":". If you want to understand that API in depth or build a custom decoration style, see the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"Decorations.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Highlights"},"Preferences.md":{"url":"Preferences.md","identifier":"Preferences.md","title":"EPUB navigator preferences","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EPUB navigator preferences"}],"type":"link"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Decorations":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/decorations","kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Decorations","title":"Decorations","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Decoration API lets you overlay visual elements on publication content – highlights, search result markers, TTS playback indicators, page-number labels in the margin, and more. For the common case of implementing user highlights, see the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"Highlights.md"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic"},"Highlights.md":{"url":"Highlights.md","identifier":"Highlights.md","title":"Highlighting guide","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Highlighting guide"}],"type":"link"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","url":"\/documentation\/readium","role":"collection","title":"Readium","type":"topic","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Readium Swift Toolkit is a toolkit for ebooks, audiobooks, and comics written in Swift & Kotlin."}]},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/SwiftUI":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Navigator is built with UIKit and provides "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" implementations. Nevertheless, you can integrate them into a SwiftUI view hierarchy using Apple’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","title":"Integrating the Navigator with SwiftUI","type":"topic","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/swiftui"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Navigator":{"type":"topic","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use a Readium Navigator to present the publication to the user. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Navigator"},{"type":"text","text":" renders resources on the screen and offers APIs and user interactions for navigating the contents."}],"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigator","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","title":"Navigator"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Preferences":{"title":"Configuring the Navigator","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Take a look at the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md"},{"type":"text","text":" if you are already using the legacy EPUB settings."}],"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/preferences","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","role":"article"},"../Migration%20Guide.md":{"url":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","title":"migration guide","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"migration guide"}],"type":"link"}}}